@NODE TRUTH "SOME TRADER TRUTHS WORTH TO HAVE A LOOK AT !!!"
  @{FG FILL}@{B}׳X׳=׳X׳=׳X׳=׳X׳=׳X׳=׳X׳=׳X׳=׳X׳=׳X׳=׳X׳=׳X׳=׳X׳=׳X׳=׳X׳=׳X׳=׳X׳=׳X׳=׳X׳@{FG TEXT}@{UB}
  @{FG FILL}@{B}     tHe iNTERNATiONAl fEDERATiOn oF fREe tRADERs iN cYBERSPACe !!     @{FG TEXT}@{UB}
  @{FG FILL}@{B}׳X׳=׳X׳=׳X׳=׳X׳=׳X׳=׳X׳=׳X׳=׳X׳=׳X׳=׳X׳=׳X׳=׳X׳=׳X׳=׳X׳=׳X׳=׳X׳=׳X׳=׳X׳@{FG TEXT}@{UB}

  @{BG FILL}@{FG HIGHLIGHT}TRADER TRUTHS:@{FG TEXT}@{BG BACKGROUND}
 
 @{fg highlight} You will get DSBLD when You don't need it anymore!@{fg text}
 
  You will lose your 3:1 ratio when you reach 1:1!
 
 @{fg highlight} A Fake on one board is not a fake on another board!@{fg text}
 
  A Major on one board is not a major on another board!
 
 @{fg highlight} You might have to inform the Sysop to get your Major!@{fg text}
 
  You might not get faked if you know the Sysop!
 
 @{fg highlight} You can get kicked out of the board for personal reasons!@{fg text}
 
  You might have to nag to get your Ax up, heavy trading isn't enough!
 
 @{fg highlight} Friendly advices, can easily be taken as criticism!@{fg text}
 
  There are no guarantees on anything!
 
 @{fg highlight} The backup of the User-Data is your only safety!@{fg text}
 
  Check your bytes before and after UL/DL, keep your scrollbacks for
  atleast a week, cause it's your only chance of proving your creds!
 
 @{fg highlight} If You trade like hell for a short time and take a break, there will@{fg text}
 @{fg highlight} be instant nagging. Better to keep a steady flow and avoid the abuse!@{fg text}
 
  When you have proven yourself as a good trader, then make sure that all
  your personal datas in the quest gets deleted! No reason to let a Sysop
  keep your adress and phone-number! Just think if the board gets busted!
 
 @{fg highlight} A Sysop who doesn't know his Amiga very well,@{fg text}
 @{fg highlight} seldom knows his Ami-Express any better!@{fg text}
 
  A Sysop requesting a file that's already online is seldom blind!
 
 @{fg highlight} All Extra-bytes are fake-bytes. Like; Request-bytes & Weektop-bonuses...@{fg text}
 @{fg highlight} So a board with 1 Gig Up, very seldom have all those bytes really traded,@{fg text}
 @{fg highlight} but the Major-bytes and the Nuked bytes might equal out some times!@{fg text}
 
  Just because we are Users, doesn't make the Sysops Givers!
 
 @{fg highlight} Anyone still lame after 6 months in the Scene, will stay lame forever!@{fg text}
 
  A Gamer is a grown-up Lamer!
  These guys should sell their modems and buy a couple of Originals with fat
  manuals, and stay happy outside the scene, instead of leeching and asking
  stupid questions on walls or in letters, like; how do I pass that monster?
 
 @{fg highlight} The expression Lamer comes from the classic saying: LameBrain@{fg text}
 @{fg highlight} A word I just heard in a b/w-movie with Sophia Loren & Clark Gable (1958).@{fg text}
 
  About 5 boards could easily handle the complete Gothenburg-Scene!
  What we have is Chewing-gum-Trading! A board with more Upload than
  Download is the Evidence for this Theory! Just check it out!
  The goal should be a Ratio of 3 download on every Major Upload!
 
 @{fg highlight} Big Iff-Adds are relatives to Fakes!@{fg text}
 
  Wildcard-Adds are relatives to Viruses!
 
 @{fg highlight} Any trader could strip his wares from adds if he wanted to, but who@{fg text}
 @{fg highlight} wants to lose those creds, when no Sysop is complaining about it?@{fg text}
 
  Many Sysops demands Sent-lines, but uses none themselves!
 
 @{fg highlight} Never ask for higher standard than your own!@{fg text}
 
  @{b}MgM/iTc@{ub} 03-Okt-94  09:23:33
@ENDNODE

